  16 ---
  17 module: openssl_certificate
  18 version_added: "2.4"
  19 short_description: Generate and/or check OpenSSL certificates
  20 description:
  21     - This module allows one to (re)generate OpenSSL certificates.
  22     - It implements a notion of provider (ie. C(selfsigned), C(ownca), C(acme), C(assertonly), C(entrust))
  23       for your certificate.
  24     - The C(assertonly) provider is intended for use cases where one is only interested in
  25       checking properties of a supplied certificate. Please note that this provider has been
  26       deprecated in Ansible 2.9 and will be removed in Ansible 2.13. See the examples on how
  27       to emulate C(assertonly) usage with M(openssl_certificate_info), M(openssl_csr_info),
  28       M(openssl_privatekey_info) and M(assert). This also allows more flexible checks than
  29       the ones offered by the C(assertonly) provider.
  30     - The C(ownca) provider is intended for generating OpenSSL certificate signed with your own
  31       CA (Certificate Authority) certificate (self-signed certificate).
  32     - Many properties that can be specified in this module are for validation of an
  33       existing or newly generated certificate. The proper place to specify them, if you
  34       want to receive a certificate with these properties is a CSR (Certificate Signing Request).
  35     - "Please note that the module regenerates existing certificate if it doesn't match the module's
  36       options, or if it seems to be corrupt. If you are concerned that this could overwrite
  37       your existing certificate, consider using the I(backup) option."
  38     - It uses the pyOpenSSL or cryptography python library to interact with OpenSSL.
  39     - If both the cryptography and PyOpenSSL libraries are available (and meet the minimum version requirements)
  40       cryptography will be preferred as a backend over PyOpenSSL (unless the backend is forced with C(select_crypto_backend)).
  41       Please note that the PyOpenSSL backend was deprecated in Ansible 2.9 and will be removed in Ansible 2.13.
  42 requirements:
  43     - PyOpenSSL >= 0.15 or cryptography >= 1.6 (if using C(selfsigned) or C(assertonly) provider)
  44     - acme-tiny >= 4.0.0 (if using the C(acme) provider)
  45 author:
  46   - Yanis Guenane (@Spredzy)
  47   - Markus Teufelberger (@MarkusTeufelberger)

  67               Please see the examples on how to emulate it with M(openssl_certificate_info), M(openssl_csr_info),
  68               M(openssl_privatekey_info) and M(assert).
  69             - "The C(entrust) provider was added for Ansible 2.9 and requires credentials for the
  70                L(Entrust Certificate Services,https://www.entrustdatacard.com/products/categories/ssl-certificates) (ECS) API."
  71             - Required if I(state) is C(present).
  72         type: str
  73         choices: [ acme, assertonly, entrust, ownca, selfsigned ]

 924     pass

 927 class Certificate(crypto_utils.OpenSSLObject):
 928 
 929     def __init__(self, module, backend):
 930         super(Certificate, self).__init__(
 931             module.params['path'],
 932             module.params['state'],
 933             module.params['force'],
 934             module.check_mode
 935         )
 936 
 937         self.provider = module.params['provider']
 938         self.privatekey_path = module.params['privatekey_path']
 939         self.privatekey_content = module.params['privatekey_content']
 940         if self.privatekey_content is not None:
 941             self.privatekey_content = self.privatekey_content.encode('utf-8')
 942         self.privatekey_passphrase = module.params['privatekey_passphrase']
 943         self.csr_path = module.params['csr_path']
 944         self.csr_content = module.params['csr_content']
 945         if self.csr_content is not None:
 946             self.csr_content = self.csr_content.encode('utf-8')
 947         self.cert = None
 948         self.privatekey = None
 949         self.csr = None
 950         self.backend = backend
 951         self.module = module
 952         self.return_content = module.params['return_content']
 953 
 954         # The following are default values which make sure check() works as
 955         # before if providers do not explicitly change these properties.
 956         self.create_subject_key_identifier = 'never_create'
 957         self.create_authority_key_identifier = False
 958 
 959         self.backup = module.params['backup']
 960         self.backup_file = None
 961 
 962     def _validate_privatekey(self):
 963         if self.backend == 'pyopenssl':
 964             ctx = OpenSSL.SSL.Context(OpenSSL.SSL.TLSv1_2_METHOD)
 965             ctx.use_privatekey(self.privatekey)
 966             ctx.use_certificate(self.cert)
 967             try:
 968                 ctx.check_privatekey()
 969                 return True
 970             except OpenSSL.SSL.Error:
 971                 return False
 972         elif self.backend == 'cryptography':
 973             return crypto_utils.cryptography_compare_public_keys(self.cert.public_key(), self.privatekey.public_key())
 974 
 975     def _validate_csr(self):
 976         if self.backend == 'pyopenssl':
 977             # Verify that CSR is signed by certificate's private key
 978             try:
 979                 self.csr.verify(self.cert.get_pubkey())
 980             except OpenSSL.crypto.Error:
 981                 return False
 982             # Check subject
 983             if self.csr.get_subject() != self.cert.get_subject():
 984                 return False
 985             # Check extensions
 986             csr_extensions = self.csr.get_extensions()
 987             cert_extension_count = self.cert.get_extension_count()
 988             if len(csr_extensions) != cert_extension_count:
 989                 return False
 990             for extension_number in range(0, cert_extension_count):
 991                 cert_extension = self.cert.get_extension(extension_number)
 992                 csr_extension = filter(lambda extension: extension.get_short_name() == cert_extension.get_short_name(), csr_extensions)
 993                 if cert_extension.get_data() != list(csr_extension)[0].get_data():
 994                     return False
 995             return True
 996         elif self.backend == 'cryptography':
 997             # Verify that CSR is signed by certificate's private key
 998             if not self.csr.is_signature_valid:
 999                 return False
1000             if not crypto_utils.cryptography_compare_public_keys(self.csr.public_key(), self.cert.public_key()):
1001                 return False
1002             # Check subject
1003             if self.csr.subject != self.cert.subject:
1004                 return False
1005             # Check extensions
1006             cert_exts = list(self.cert.extensions)
1007             csr_exts = list(self.csr.extensions)
1008             if self.create_subject_key_identifier != 'never_create':
1009                 # Filter out SubjectKeyIdentifier extension before comparison
1010                 cert_exts = list(filter(lambda x: not isinstance(x.value, x509.SubjectKeyIdentifier), cert_exts))
1011                 csr_exts = list(filter(lambda x: not isinstance(x.value, x509.SubjectKeyIdentifier), csr_exts))
1012             if self.create_authority_key_identifier:
1013                 # Filter out AuthorityKeyIdentifier extension before comparison
1014                 cert_exts = list(filter(lambda x: not isinstance(x.value, x509.AuthorityKeyIdentifier), cert_exts))
1015                 csr_exts = list(filter(lambda x: not isinstance(x.value, x509.AuthorityKeyIdentifier), csr_exts))
1016             if len(cert_exts) != len(csr_exts):
1017                 return False
1018             for cert_ext in cert_exts:
1019                 try:
1020                     csr_ext = self.csr.extensions.get_extension_for_oid(cert_ext.oid)
1021                     if cert_ext != csr_ext:
1022                         return False
1023                 except cryptography.x509.ExtensionNotFound as dummy:
1024                     return False
1025             return True
1026 
1027     def remove(self, module):
1028         if self.backup:
1029             self.backup_file = module.backup_local(self.path)
1030         super(Certificate, self).remove(module)
1031 
1032     def check(self, module, perms_required=True):
1033         """Ensure the resource is in its desired state."""
1034 
1035         state_and_perms = super(Certificate, self).check(module, perms_required)
1036 
1037         if not state_and_perms:
1038             return False
1039 
1040         try:
1041             self.cert = crypto_utils.load_certificate(self.path, backend=self.backend)
1042         except Exception as dummy:
1043             return False
1044 
1045         if self.privatekey_path or self.privatekey_content:
1046             try:
1047                 self.privatekey = crypto_utils.load_privatekey(
1048                     path=self.privatekey_path,
1049                     content=self.privatekey_content,
1050                     passphrase=self.privatekey_passphrase,
1051                     backend=self.backend
1052                 )
1053             except crypto_utils.OpenSSLBadPassphraseError as exc:
1054                 raise CertificateError(exc)
1055             if not self._validate_privatekey():
1056                 return False
1057 
1058         if self.csr_path or self.csr_content:
1059             self.csr = crypto_utils.load_certificate_request(
1060                 path=self.csr_path,
1061                 content=self.csr_content,
1062                 backend=self.backend
1063             )
1064             if not self._validate_csr():
1065                 return False
1066 
1067         # Check SubjectKeyIdentifier
1068         if self.backend == 'cryptography' and self.create_subject_key_identifier != 'never_create':
1069             # Get hold of certificate's SKI
1070             try:
1071                 ext = self.cert.extensions.get_extension_for_class(x509.SubjectKeyIdentifier)
1072             except cryptography.x509.ExtensionNotFound as dummy:
1073                 return False
1074             # Get hold of CSR's SKI for 'create_if_not_provided'
1075             csr_ext = None
1076             if self.create_subject_key_identifier == 'create_if_not_provided':
1077                 try:
1078                     csr_ext = self.csr.extensions.get_extension_for_class(x509.SubjectKeyIdentifier)
1079                 except cryptography.x509.ExtensionNotFound as dummy:
1080                     pass
1081             if csr_ext is None:
1082                 # If CSR had no SKI, or we chose to ignore it ('always_create'), compare with created SKI
1083                 if ext.value.digest != x509.SubjectKeyIdentifier.from_public_key(self.cert.public_key()).digest:
1084                     return False
1085             else:
1086                 # If CSR had SKI and we didn't ignore it ('create_if_not_provided'), compare SKIs
1087                 if ext.value.digest != csr_ext.value.digest:
1088                     return False
1089 
1090         return True
1091

1284 
1285         if self.privatekey_content is None and not os.path.exists(self.privatekey_path):
1286             raise CertificateError(

1331

1334                 'notBefore': self.notBefore,
1335                 'notAfter': self.notAfter,
1336                 'serial_number': self.serial_number,

1589         )
1590         try:
1591             self.ca_privatekey = crypto_utils.load_privatekey(
1592                 path=self.ca_privatekey_path,
1593                 content=self.ca_privatekey_content,
1594                 passphrase=self.ca_privatekey_passphrase
1595             )
1596         except crypto_utils.OpenSSLBadPassphraseError as exc:
1597             module.fail_json(msg=str(exc))

1599     def generate(self, module):
1600 
1601         if self.ca_cert_content is None and not os.path.exists(self.ca_cert_path):
1602             raise CertificateError(
1603                 'The CA certificate %s does not exist' % self.ca_cert_path
1604             )
1605 
1606         if self.ca_privatekey_content is None and not os.path.exists(self.ca_privatekey_path):
1607             raise CertificateError(
1608                 'The CA private key %s does not exist' % self.ca_privatekey_path
1609             )
1610 
1611         if self.csr_content is None and not os.path.exists(self.csr_path):
1612             raise CertificateError(
1613                 'The certificate signing request file %s does not exist' % self.csr_path
1614             )
1615 
1616         if not self.check(module, perms_required=False) or self.force:
1617             cert = crypto.X509()
1618             cert.set_serial_number(self.serial_number)
1619             cert.set_notBefore(to_bytes(self.notBefore))
1620             cert.set_notAfter(to_bytes(self.notAfter))
1621             cert.set_subject(self.csr.get_subject())
1622             cert.set_issuer(self.ca_cert.get_subject())
1623             cert.set_version(self.version - 1)
1624             cert.set_pubkey(self.csr.get_pubkey())
1625             cert.add_extensions(self.csr.get_extensions())
1626 
1627             cert.sign(self.ca_privatekey, self.digest)
1628             self.cert = cert
1629 
1630             if self.backup:
1631                 self.backup_file = module.backup_local(self.path)
1632             crypto_utils.write_file(module, crypto.dump_certificate(crypto.FILETYPE_PEM, self.cert))
1633             self.changed = True
1634 
1635         file_args = module.load_file_common_arguments(module.params)
1636         if module.set_fs_attributes_if_different(file_args, False):
1637             self.changed = True

1644             'privatekey': self.privatekey_path,
1645             'csr': self.csr_path,

1671 def compare_sets(subset, superset, equality=False):
1672     if equality:
1673         return set(subset) == set(superset)
1674     else:
1675         return all(x in superset for x in subset)
1676 
1677 
1678 def compare_dicts(subset, superset, equality=False):
1679     if equality:
1680         return subset == superset
1681     else:
1682         return all(superset.get(x) == v for x, v in subset.items())

1811     def assertonly(self, module):
1812         messages = []
1813         if self.privatekey_path is not None or self.privatekey_content is not None:
1814             if not self._validate_privatekey():
1815                 messages.append(
1816                     'Certificate %s and private key %s do not match' %
1817                     (self.path, self.privatekey_path or '(provided in module options)')
1818                 )
1819 
1820         if self.csr_path is not None or self.csr_content is not None:
1821             if not self._validate_csr_signature():
1822                 messages.append(
1823                     'Certificate %s and CSR %s do not match: private key mismatch' %
1824                     (self.path, self.csr_path or '(provided in module options)')
1825                 )
1826             if not self._validate_csr_subject():
1827                 messages.append(
1828                     'Certificate %s and CSR %s do not match: subject mismatch' %
1829                     (self.path, self.csr_path or '(provided in module options)')
1830                 )
1831             if not self._validate_csr_extensions():
1832                 messages.append(
1833                     'Certificate %s and CSR %s do not match: extensions mismatch' %
1834                     (self.path, self.csr_path or '(provided in module options)')
1835                 )
1836 
1837         if self.signature_algorithms is not None:
1838             wrong_alg = self._validate_signature_algorithms()
1839             if wrong_alg:
1840                 messages.append(
1841                     'Invalid signature algorithm (got %s, expected one of %s)' %
1842                     (wrong_alg, self.signature_algorithms)
1843                 )
1844 
1845         if self.subject is not None:
1846             failure = self._validate_subject()
1847             if failure:
1848                 dummy, cert_subject = failure
1849                 messages.append(
1850                     'Invalid subject component (got %s, expected all of %s to be present)' %
1851                     (cert_subject, self.subject)
1852                 )
1853 
1854         if self.issuer is not None:
1855             failure = self._validate_issuer()
1856             if failure:
1857                 dummy, cert_issuer = failure
1858                 messages.append(
1859                     'Invalid issuer component (got %s, expected all of %s to be present)' % (cert_issuer, self.issuer)
1860                 )
1861 
1862         if self.has_expired is not None:
1863             cert_expired = self._validate_has_expired()
1864             if cert_expired != self.has_expired:
1865                 messages.append(
1866                     'Certificate expiration check failed (certificate expiration is %s, expected %s)' %
1867                     (cert_expired, self.has_expired)
1868                 )
1869 
1870         if self.version is not None:
1871             cert_version = self._validate_version()
1872             if cert_version != self.version:
1873                 messages.append(
1874                     'Invalid certificate version number (got %s, expected %s)' %
1875                     (cert_version, self.version)
1876                 )
1877 
1878         if self.key_usage is not None:
1879             failure = self._validate_key_usage()
1880             if failure == NO_EXTENSION:
1881                 messages.append('Found no keyUsage extension')
1882             elif failure:
1883                 dummy, cert_key_usage = failure
1884                 messages.append(
1885                     'Invalid keyUsage components (got %s, expected all of %s to be present)' %
1886                     (cert_key_usage, self.key_usage)
1887                 )
1888 
1889         if self.extended_key_usage is not None:
1890             failure = self._validate_extended_key_usage()
1891             if failure == NO_EXTENSION:
1892                 messages.append('Found no extendedKeyUsage extension')
1893             elif failure:
1894                 dummy, ext_cert_key_usage = failure
1895                 messages.append(
1896                     'Invalid extendedKeyUsage component (got %s, expected all of %s to be present)' % (ext_cert_key_usage, self.extended_key_usage)
1897                 )
1898 
1899         if self.subject_alt_name is not None:
1900             failure = self._validate_subject_alt_name()
1901             if failure == NO_EXTENSION:
1902                 messages.append('Found no subjectAltName extension')
1903             elif failure:
1904                 dummy, cert_san = failure
1905                 messages.append(
1906                     'Invalid subjectAltName component (got %s, expected all of %s to be present)' %
1907                     (cert_san, self.subject_alt_name)
1908                 )
1909 
1910         if self.not_before is not None:
1911             cert_not_valid_before = self._validate_not_before()
1912             if cert_not_valid_before != crypto_utils.get_relative_time_option(self.not_before, 'not_before', backend=self.backend):
1913                 messages.append(
1914                     'Invalid not_before component (got %s, expected %s to be present)' %
1915                     (cert_not_valid_before, self.not_before)
1916                 )
1917 
1918         if self.not_after is not None:
1919             cert_not_valid_after = self._validate_not_after()
1920             if cert_not_valid_after != crypto_utils.get_relative_time_option(self.not_after, 'not_after', backend=self.backend):
1921                 messages.append(
1922                     'Invalid not_after component (got %s, expected %s to be present)' %
1923                     (cert_not_valid_after, self.not_after)
1924                 )
1925 
1926         if self.valid_at is not None:
1927             not_before, valid_at, not_after = self._validate_valid_at()
1928             if not (not_before <= valid_at <= not_after):
1929                 messages.append(
1930                     'Certificate is not valid for the specified date (%s) - not_before: %s - not_after: %s' %
1931                     (self.valid_at, not_before, not_after)
1932                 )
1933 
1934         if self.invalid_at is not None:
1935             not_before, invalid_at, not_after = self._validate_invalid_at()
1936             if not_before <= invalid_at <= not_after:
1937                 messages.append(
1938                     'Certificate is not invalid for the specified date (%s) - not_before: %s - not_after: %s' %
1939                     (self.invalid_at, not_before, not_after)
1940                 )
1941 
1942         if self.valid_in is not None:
1943             not_before, valid_in, not_after = self._validate_valid_in()
1944             if not not_before <= valid_in <= not_after:
1945                 messages.append(
1946                     'Certificate is not valid in %s from now (that would be %s) - not_before: %s - not_after: %s' %
1947                     (self.valid_in, valid_in, not_before, not_after)
1948                 )
1949         return messages

1980     def _validate_privatekey(self):

1983     def _validate_csr_signature(self):
1984         if not self.csr.is_signature_valid:
1985             return False

1991     def _validate_csr_extensions(self):
1992         cert_exts = self.cert.extensions
1993         csr_exts = self.csr.extensions
1994         if len(cert_exts) != len(csr_exts):
1995             return False
1996         for cert_ext in cert_exts:
1997             try:
1998                 csr_ext = csr_exts.get_extension_for_oid(cert_ext.oid)
1999                 if cert_ext != csr_ext:
2000                     return False
2001             except cryptography.x509.ExtensionNotFound as dummy:
2002                 return False
2003         return True

2007             return self.cert.signature_algorithm_oid._name

2009     def _validate_subject(self):
2010         expected_subject = Name([NameAttribute(oid=crypto_utils.cryptography_name_to_oid(sub[0]), value=to_text(sub[1]))
2011                                  for sub in self.subject])
2012         cert_subject = self.cert.subject
2013         if not compare_sets(expected_subject, cert_subject, self.subject_strict):
2014             return expected_subject, cert_subject
2015 
2016     def _validate_issuer(self):

2018                                 for iss in self.issuer])

2020         if not compare_sets(expected_issuer, cert_issuer, self.issuer_strict):
2021             return self.issuer, cert_issuer

2023     def _validate_has_expired(self):
2024         cert_not_after = self.cert.not_valid_after
2025         cert_expired = cert_not_after < datetime.datetime.utcnow()
2026         return cert_expired

2028     def _validate_version(self):
2029         if self.cert.version == x509.Version.v1:
2030             return 1
2031         if self.cert.version == x509.Version.v3:
2032             return 3
2033         return "unknown"

2035     def _validate_key_usage(self):
2036         try:
2037             current_key_usage = self.cert.extensions.get_extension_for_class(x509.KeyUsage).value
2038             test_key_usage = dict(
2039                 digital_signature=current_key_usage.digital_signature,
2040                 content_commitment=current_key_usage.content_commitment,
2041                 key_encipherment=current_key_usage.key_encipherment,
2042                 data_encipherment=current_key_usage.data_encipherment,
2043                 key_agreement=current_key_usage.key_agreement,
2044                 key_cert_sign=current_key_usage.key_cert_sign,
2045                 crl_sign=current_key_usage.crl_sign,
2046                 encipher_only=False,
2047                 decipher_only=False
2048             )
2049             if test_key_usage['key_agreement']:
2050                 test_key_usage.update(dict(
2051                     encipher_only=current_key_usage.encipher_only,
2052                     decipher_only=current_key_usage.decipher_only
2053                 ))
2054 
2055             key_usages = crypto_utils.cryptography_parse_key_usage_params(self.key_usage)
2056             if not compare_dicts(key_usages, test_key_usage, self.key_usage_strict):
2057                 return self.key_usage, [k for k, v in test_key_usage.items() if v is True]
2058 
2059         except cryptography.x509.ExtensionNotFound:
2060             # This is only bad if the user specified a non-empty list
2061             if self.key_usage:
2062                 return NO_EXTENSION
2063 
2064     def _validate_extended_key_usage(self):
2065         try:
2066             current_ext_keyusage = self.cert.extensions.get_extension_for_class(x509.ExtendedKeyUsage).value
2067             usages = [crypto_utils.cryptography_name_to_oid(usage) for usage in self.extended_key_usage]
2068             expected_ext_keyusage = x509.ExtendedKeyUsage(usages)
2069             if not compare_sets(expected_ext_keyusage, current_ext_keyusage, self.extended_key_usage_strict):
2070                 return [eku.value for eku in expected_ext_keyusage], [eku.value for eku in current_ext_keyusage]
2071 
2072         except cryptography.x509.ExtensionNotFound:
2073             # This is only bad if the user specified a non-empty list
2074             if self.extended_key_usage:
2075                 return NO_EXTENSION
2076 
2077     def _validate_subject_alt_name(self):

2080             expected_san = [crypto_utils.cryptography_get_name(san) for san in self.subject_alt_name]

2083         except cryptography.x509.ExtensionNotFound:
2084             # This is only bad if the user specified a non-empty list
2085             if self.subject_alt_name:
2086                 return NO_EXTENSION

2125             elif isinstance(attr, dict):

2130     def _validate_privatekey(self):
2131         ctx = OpenSSL.SSL.Context(OpenSSL.SSL.TLSv1_2_METHOD)
2132         ctx.use_privatekey(self.privatekey)
2133         ctx.use_certificate(self.cert)
2134         try:
2135             ctx.check_privatekey()
2136             return True
2137         except OpenSSL.SSL.Error:
2138             return False

2140     def _validate_csr_signature(self):
2141         try:
2142             self.csr.verify(self.cert.get_pubkey())
2143         except OpenSSL.crypto.Error:
2144             return False

2146     def _validate_csr_subject(self):

2150     def _validate_csr_extensions(self):
2151         csr_extensions = self.csr.get_extensions()
2152         cert_extension_count = self.cert.get_extension_count()
2153         if len(csr_extensions) != cert_extension_count:
2154             return False
2155         for extension_number in range(0, cert_extension_count):
2156             cert_extension = self.cert.get_extension(extension_number)
2157             csr_extension = filter(lambda extension: extension.get_short_name() == cert_extension.get_short_name(), csr_extensions)
2158             if cert_extension.get_data() != list(csr_extension)[0].get_data():
2159                 return False

2166     def _validate_subject(self):
2167         expected_subject = [(OpenSSL._util.lib.OBJ_txt2nid(sub[0]), sub[1]) for sub in self.subject]
2168         cert_subject = self.cert.get_subject().get_components()
2169         current_subject = [(OpenSSL._util.lib.OBJ_txt2nid(sub[0]), sub[1]) for sub in cert_subject]
2170         if not compare_sets(expected_subject, current_subject, self.subject_strict):
2171             return expected_subject, current_subject
2172 
2173     def _validate_issuer(self):
2174         expected_issuer = [(OpenSSL._util.lib.OBJ_txt2nid(iss[0]), iss[1]) for iss in self.issuer]
2175         cert_issuer = self.cert.get_issuer().get_components()
2176         current_issuer = [(OpenSSL._util.lib.OBJ_txt2nid(iss[0]), iss[1]) for iss in cert_issuer]
2177         if not compare_sets(expected_issuer, current_issuer, self.issuer_strict):
2178             return self.issuer, cert_issuer
2179 
2180     def _validate_has_expired(self):
2181         # The following 3 lines are the same as the current PyOpenSSL code for cert.has_expired().
2182         # Older version of PyOpenSSL have a buggy implementation,
2183         # to avoid issues with those we added the code from a more recent release here.
2184 
2185         time_string = to_native(self.cert.get_notAfter())
2186         not_after = datetime.datetime.strptime(time_string, "%Y%m%d%H%M%SZ")
2187         cert_expired = not_after < datetime.datetime.utcnow()
2188         return cert_expired
2189 
2190     def _validate_version(self):
2191         # Version numbers in certs are off by one:
2192         # v1: 0, v2: 1, v3: 2 ...
2193         return self.cert.get_version() + 1
2194 
2195     def _validate_key_usage(self):
2196         found = False
2197         for extension_idx in range(0, self.cert.get_extension_count()):
2198             extension = self.cert.get_extension(extension_idx)
2199             if extension.get_short_name() == b'keyUsage':
2200                 found = True
2201                 expected_extension = crypto.X509Extension(b"keyUsage", False, b', '.join(self.key_usage))
2202                 key_usage = [usage.strip() for usage in to_text(expected_extension, errors='surrogate_or_strict').split(',')]
2203                 current_ku = [usage.strip() for usage in to_text(extension, errors='surrogate_or_strict').split(',')]
2204                 if not compare_sets(key_usage, current_ku, self.key_usage_strict):
2205                     return self.key_usage, str(extension).split(', ')
2206         if not found:
2207             # This is only bad if the user specified a non-empty list
2208             if self.key_usage:
2209                 return NO_EXTENSION
2210 
2211     def _validate_extended_key_usage(self):
2212         found = False
2213         for extension_idx in range(0, self.cert.get_extension_count()):
2214             extension = self.cert.get_extension(extension_idx)
2215             if extension.get_short_name() == b'extendedKeyUsage':
2216                 found = True
2217                 extKeyUsage = [OpenSSL._util.lib.OBJ_txt2nid(keyUsage) for keyUsage in self.extended_key_usage]
2218                 current_xku = [OpenSSL._util.lib.OBJ_txt2nid(usage.strip()) for usage in
2219                                to_bytes(extension, errors='surrogate_or_strict').split(b',')]
2220                 if not compare_sets(extKeyUsage, current_xku, self.extended_key_usage_strict):
2221                     return self.extended_key_usage, str(extension).split(', ')
2222         if not found:
2223             # This is only bad if the user specified a non-empty list
2224             if self.extended_key_usage:
2225                 return NO_EXTENSION
2226 
2227     def _normalize_san(self, san):
2228         # Apparently OpenSSL returns 'IP address' not 'IP' as specifier when converting the subjectAltName to string
2229         # although it won't accept this specifier when generating the CSR. (https://github.com/openssl/openssl/issues/4004)
2230         if san.startswith('IP Address:'):
2231             san = 'IP:' + san[len('IP Address:'):]
2232         if san.startswith('IP:'):
2233             ip = compat_ipaddress.ip_address(san[3:])
2234             san = 'IP:{0}'.format(ip.compressed)
2235         return san
2236 
2237     def _validate_subject_alt_name(self):
2238         found = False
2239         for extension_idx in range(0, self.cert.get_extension_count()):
2240             extension = self.cert.get_extension(extension_idx)
2241             if extension.get_short_name() == b'subjectAltName':
2242                 found = True
2243                 l_altnames = [self._normalize_san(altname.strip()) for altname in
2244                               to_text(extension, errors='surrogate_or_strict').split(', ')]
2245                 sans = [self._normalize_san(to_text(san, errors='surrogate_or_strict')) for san in self.subject_alt_name]
2246                 if not compare_sets(sans, l_altnames, self.subject_alt_name_strict):
2247                     return self.subject_alt_name, l_altnames
2248         if not found:
2249             # This is only bad if the user specified a non-empty list
2250             if self.subject_alt_name:
2251                 return NO_EXTENSION
2252 
2253     def _validate_not_before(self):
2254         return self.cert.get_notBefore()
2255 
2256     def _validate_not_after(self):
2257         return self.cert.get_notAfter()
2258 
2259     def _validate_valid_at(self):
2260         rt = crypto_utils.get_relative_time_option(self.valid_at, "valid_at", backend=self.backend)
2261         rt = to_bytes(rt, errors='surrogate_or_strict')
2262         return self.cert.get_notBefore(), rt, self.cert.get_notAfter()
2263 
2264     def _validate_invalid_at(self):
2265         rt = crypto_utils.get_relative_time_option(self.invalid_at, "invalid_at", backend=self.backend)
2266         rt = to_bytes(rt, errors='surrogate_or_strict')

2269     def _validate_valid_in(self):

2271         valid_in_date = to_bytes(valid_in_asn1, errors='surrogate_or_strict')
2272         return self.cert.get_notBefore(), valid_in_date, self.cert.get_notAfter()

2275 class EntrustCertificate(Certificate):
2276     """Retrieve a certificate using Entrust (ECS)."""
2277 
2278     def __init__(self, module, backend):
2279         super(EntrustCertificate, self).__init__(module, backend)
2280         self.trackingId = None
2281         self.notAfter = crypto_utils.get_relative_time_option(module.params['entrust_not_after'], 'entrust_not_after', backend=self.backend)
2282 
2283         if self.csr_content is None or not os.path.exists(self.csr_path):
2284             raise CertificateError(
2285                 'The certificate signing request file {0} does not exist'.format(self.csr_path)
2286             )
2287 
2288         self.csr = crypto_utils.load_certificate_request(
2289             path=self.csr_path,
2290             content=self.csr_content,
2291             backend=self.backend,
2292         )
2293 
2294         # ECS API defaults to using the validated organization tied to the account.
2295         # We want to always force behavior of trying to use the organization provided in the CSR.
2296         # To that end we need to parse out the organization from the CSR.
2297         self.csr_org = None
2298         if self.backend == 'pyopenssl':
2299             csr_subject = self.csr.get_subject()
2300             csr_subject_components = csr_subject.get_components()
2301             for k, v in csr_subject_components:
2302                 if k.upper() == 'O':
2303                     # Entrust does not support multiple validated organizations in a single certificate
2304                     if self.csr_org is not None:
2305                         module.fail_json(msg=("Entrust provider does not currently support multiple validated organizations. Multiple organizations found in "
2306                                               "Subject DN: '{0}'. ".format(csr_subject)))
2307                     else:
2308                         self.csr_org = v
2309         elif self.backend == 'cryptography':
2310             csr_subject_orgs = self.csr.subject.get_attributes_for_oid(NameOID.ORGANIZATION_NAME)
2311             if len(csr_subject_orgs) == 1:
2312                 self.csr_org = csr_subject_orgs[0].value
2313             elif len(csr_subject_orgs) > 1:
2314                 module.fail_json(msg=("Entrust provider does not currently support multiple validated organizations. Multiple organizations found in "
2315                                       "Subject DN: '{0}'. ".format(self.csr.subject)))
2316         # If no organization in the CSR, explicitly tell ECS that it should be blank in issued cert, not defaulted to
2317         # organization tied to the account.
2318         if self.csr_org is None:
2319             self.csr_org = ''
2320 
2321         try:
2322             self.ecs_client = ECSClient(
2323                 entrust_api_user=module.params.get('entrust_api_user'),
2324                 entrust_api_key=module.params.get('entrust_api_key'),
2325                 entrust_api_cert=module.params.get('entrust_api_client_cert_path'),
2326                 entrust_api_cert_key=module.params.get('entrust_api_client_cert_key_path'),
2327                 entrust_api_specification_path=module.params.get('entrust_api_specification_path')
2328             )
2329         except SessionConfigurationException as e:
2330             module.fail_json(msg='Failed to initialize Entrust Provider: {0}'.format(to_native(e.message)))
2331 
2332     def generate(self, module):
2333 
2334         if not self.check(module, perms_required=False) or self.force:
2335             # Read the CSR that was generated for us
2336             body = {}
2337             if self.csr_content is not None:
2338                 body['csr'] = self.csr_content
2339             else:
2340                 with open(self.csr_path, 'r') as csr_file:
2341                     body['csr'] = csr_file.read()
2342 
2343             body['certType'] = module.params['entrust_cert_type']
2344 
2345             # Handle expiration (30 days if not specified)
2346             expiry = self.notAfter
2347             if not expiry:
2348                 gmt_now = datetime.datetime.fromtimestamp(time.mktime(time.gmtime()))
2349                 expiry = gmt_now + datetime.timedelta(days=365)
2350 
2351             expiry_iso3339 = expiry.strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.00Z")
2352             body['certExpiryDate'] = expiry_iso3339
2353             body['org'] = self.csr_org
2354             body['tracking'] = {
2355                 'requesterName': module.params['entrust_requester_name'],
2356                 'requesterEmail': module.params['entrust_requester_email'],
2357                 'requesterPhone': module.params['entrust_requester_phone'],
2358             }
2359 
2360             try:
2361                 result = self.ecs_client.NewCertRequest(Body=body)
2362                 self.trackingId = result.get('trackingId')
2363             except RestOperationException as e:
2364                 module.fail_json(msg='Failed to request new certificate from Entrust Certificate Services (ECS): {0}'.format(to_native(e.message)))
2365 
2366             if self.backup:
2367                 self.backup_file = module.backup_local(self.path)
2368             crypto_utils.write_file(module, to_bytes(result.get('endEntityCert')))
2369             self.cert = crypto_utils.load_certificate(self.path, backend=self.backend)
2370             self.changed = True
2371 
2372     def check(self, module, perms_required=True):
2373         """Ensure the resource is in its desired state."""
2374 
2375         parent_check = super(EntrustCertificate, self).check(module, perms_required)
2376 
2377         try:
2378             cert_details = self._get_cert_details()
2379         except RestOperationException as e:
2380             module.fail_json(msg='Failed to get status of existing certificate from Entrust Certificate Services (ECS): {0}.'.format(to_native(e.message)))
2381 
2382         # Always issue a new certificate if the certificate is expired, suspended or revoked
2383         status = cert_details.get('status', False)
2384         if status == 'EXPIRED' or status == 'SUSPENDED' or status == 'REVOKED':
2385             return False
2386 
2387         # If the requested cert type was specified and it is for a different certificate type than the initial certificate, a new one is needed
2388         if module.params['entrust_cert_type'] and cert_details.get('certType') and module.params['entrust_cert_type'] != cert_details.get('certType'):
2389             return False
2390 
2391         return parent_check
2392 
2393     def _get_cert_details(self):
2394         cert_details = {}
2395         if self.cert:
2396             serial_number = None
2397             expiry = None
2398             if self.backend == 'pyopenssl':
2399                 serial_number = "{0:X}".format(self.cert.get_serial_number())
2400                 time_string = to_native(self.cert.get_notAfter())
2401                 expiry = datetime.datetime.strptime(time_string, "%Y%m%d%H%M%SZ")
2402             elif self.backend == 'cryptography':
2403                 serial_number = "{0:X}".format(self.cert.serial_number)
2404                 expiry = self.cert.not_valid_after
2405 
2406             # get some information about the expiry of this certificate
2407             expiry_iso3339 = expiry.strftime("%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.00Z")
2408             cert_details['expiresAfter'] = expiry_iso3339
2409 
2410             # If a trackingId is not already defined (from the result of a generate)
2411             # use the serial number to identify the tracking Id
2412             if self.trackingId is None and serial_number is not None:
2413                 cert_results = self.ecs_client.GetCertificates(serialNumber=serial_number).get('certificates', {})
2414 
2415                 # Finding 0 or more than 1 result is a very unlikely use case, it simply means we cannot perform additional checks
2416                 # on the 'state' as returned by Entrust Certificate Services (ECS). The general certificate validity is
2417                 # still checked as it is in the rest of the module.
2418                 if len(cert_results) == 1:
2419                     self.trackingId = cert_results[0].get('trackingId')
2420 
2421         if self.trackingId is not None:
2422             cert_details.update(self.ecs_client.GetCertificate(trackingId=self.trackingId))
2423 
2424         return cert_details
2425 
2426     def dump(self, check_mode=False):
2427 
2428         result = {
2429             'changed': self.changed,
2430             'filename': self.path,
2431             'privatekey': self.privatekey_path,
2432             'csr': self.csr_path,
2433         }
2434 
2435         if self.backup_file:
2436             result['backup_file'] = self.backup_file
2437         if self.return_content:
2438             content = crypto_utils.load_file_if_exists(self.path, ignore_errors=True)
2439             result['certificate'] = content.decode('utf-8') if content else None
2440 
2441         result.update(self._get_cert_details())
2442 
2443         return result

2446 class AcmeCertificate(Certificate):
2447     """Retrieve a certificate using the ACME protocol."""
2448 
2449     # Since there's no real use of the backend,
2450     # other than the 'self.check' function, we just pass the backend to the constructor
2451 
2452     def __init__(self, module, backend):
2453         super(AcmeCertificate, self).__init__(module, backend)
2454         self.accountkey_path = module.params['acme_accountkey_path']
2455         self.challenge_path = module.params['acme_challenge_path']
2456         self.use_chain = module.params['acme_chain']
2457         self.acme_directory = module.params['acme_directory']
2458 
2459     def generate(self, module):
2460 
2461         if self.csr_content is None and not os.path.exists(self.csr_path):
2462             raise CertificateError(
2463                 'The certificate signing request file %s does not exist' % self.csr_path
2464             )
2465 
2466         if not os.path.exists(self.accountkey_path):
2467             raise CertificateError(
2468                 'The account key %s does not exist' % self.accountkey_path
2469             )
2470 
2471         if not os.path.exists(self.challenge_path):
2472             raise CertificateError(
2473                 'The challenge path %s does not exist' % self.challenge_path
2474             )
2475 
2476         if not self.check(module, perms_required=False) or self.force:
2477             acme_tiny_path = self.module.get_bin_path('acme-tiny', required=True)
2478             command = [acme_tiny_path]
2479             if self.use_chain:
2480                 command.append('--chain')
2481             command.extend(['--account-key', self.accountkey_path])
2482             if self.csr_content is not None:
2483                 # We need to temporarily write the CSR to disk
2484                 fd, tmpsrc = tempfile.mkstemp()
2485                 module.add_cleanup_file(tmpsrc)  # Ansible will delete the file on exit
2486                 f = os.fdopen(fd, 'wb')
2487                 try:
2488                     f.write(self.csr_content)
2489                 except Exception as err:
2490                     try:
2491                         f.close()
2492                     except Exception as dummy:
2493                         pass
2494                     module.fail_json(
2495                         msg="failed to create temporary CSR file: %s" % to_native(err),
2496                         exception=traceback.format_exc()
2497                     )
2498                 f.close()
2499                 command.extend(['--csr', tmpsrc])
2500             else:
2501                 command.extend(['--csr', self.csr_path])
2502             command.extend(['--acme-dir', self.challenge_path])
2503             command.extend(['--directory-url', self.acme_directory])
2504 
2505             try:
2506                 crt = module.run_command(command, check_rc=True)[1]
2507                 if self.backup:
2508                     self.backup_file = module.backup_local(self.path)
2509                 crypto_utils.write_file(module, to_bytes(crt))
2510                 self.changed = True
2511             except OSError as exc:
2512                 raise CertificateError(exc)
2513 
2514         file_args = module.load_file_common_arguments(module.params)
2515         if module.set_fs_attributes_if_different(file_args, False):
2516             self.changed = True
2517 
2518     def dump(self, check_mode=False):
2519 
2520         result = {
2521             'changed': self.changed,
2522             'filename': self.path,
2523             'privatekey': self.privatekey_path,
2524             'accountkey': self.accountkey_path,
2525             'csr': self.csr_path,
2526         }
2527         if self.backup_file:
2528             result['backup_file'] = self.backup_file
2529         if self.return_content:
2530             content = crypto_utils.load_file_if_exists(self.path, ignore_errors=True)
2531             result['certificate'] = content.decode('utf-8') if content else None
2532 
2533         return result

2639         if module.params['state'] == 'absent':
2640             certificate = CertificateAbsent(module)
2641 
2642         else:
2643             if module.params['provider'] != 'assertonly' and module.params['csr_path'] is None and module.params['csr_content'] is None:
2644                 module.fail_json(msg='csr_path or csr_content is required when provider is not assertonly')
2645 
2646             base_dir = os.path.dirname(module.params['path']) or '.'
2647             if not os.path.isdir(base_dir):
2648                 module.fail_json(
2649                     name=base_dir,
2650                     msg='The directory %s does not exist or the file is not a directory' % base_dir
2651                 )
2652 
2653             provider = module.params['provider']
2654             if provider == 'assertonly':
2655                 module.deprecate("The 'assertonly' provider is deprecated; please see the examples of "
2656                                  "the 'openssl_certificate' module on how to replace it with other modules",
2657                                  version='2.13', collection_name='ansible.builtin')
2658             elif provider == 'selfsigned':
2659                 if module.params['privatekey_path'] is None and module.params['privatekey_content'] is None:
2660                     module.fail_json(msg='One of privatekey_path and privatekey_content must be specified for the selfsigned provider.')
2661             elif provider == 'acme':
2662                 if module.params['acme_accountkey_path'] is None:
2663                     module.fail_json(msg='The acme_accountkey_path option must be specified for the acme provider.')
2664                 if module.params['acme_challenge_path'] is None:
2665                     module.fail_json(msg='The acme_challenge_path option must be specified for the acme provider.')
2666             elif provider == 'ownca':
2667                 if module.params['ownca_path'] is None and module.params['ownca_content'] is None:
2668                     module.fail_json(msg='One of ownca_path and ownca_content must be specified for the ownca provider.')
2669                 if module.params['ownca_privatekey_path'] is None and module.params['ownca_privatekey_content'] is None:
2670                     module.fail_json(msg='One of ownca_privatekey_path and ownca_privatekey_content must be specified for the ownca provider.')
2671 
2672             backend = module.params['select_crypto_backend']
2673             if backend == 'auto':
2674                 # Detect what backend we can use
2675                 can_use_cryptography = CRYPTOGRAPHY_FOUND and CRYPTOGRAPHY_VERSION >= LooseVersion(MINIMAL_CRYPTOGRAPHY_VERSION)
2676                 can_use_pyopenssl = PYOPENSSL_FOUND and PYOPENSSL_VERSION >= LooseVersion(MINIMAL_PYOPENSSL_VERSION)
2677 
2678                 # If cryptography is available we'll use it
2679                 if can_use_cryptography:
2680                     backend = 'cryptography'
2681                 elif can_use_pyopenssl:
2682                     backend = 'pyopenssl'
2683 
2684                 if module.params['selfsigned_version'] == 2 or module.params['ownca_version'] == 2:
2685                     module.warn('crypto backend forced to pyopenssl. The cryptography library does not support v2 certificates')
2686                     backend = 'pyopenssl'
2687 
2688                 # Fail if no backend has been found
2689                 if backend == 'auto':
2690                     module.fail_json(msg=("Can't detect any of the required Python libraries "
2691                                           "cryptography (>= {0}) or PyOpenSSL (>= {1})").format(
2692                                               MINIMAL_CRYPTOGRAPHY_VERSION,
2693                                               MINIMAL_PYOPENSSL_VERSION))
2694 
2695             if backend == 'pyopenssl':
2696                 if not PYOPENSSL_FOUND:
2697                     module.fail_json(msg=missing_required_lib('pyOpenSSL >= {0}'.format(MINIMAL_PYOPENSSL_VERSION)),
2698                                      exception=PYOPENSSL_IMP_ERR)
2699                 if module.params['provider'] in ['selfsigned', 'ownca', 'assertonly']:
2700                     try:
2701                         getattr(crypto.X509Req, 'get_extensions')
2702                     except AttributeError:
2703                         module.fail_json(msg='You need to have PyOpenSSL>=0.15')
2704 
2705                 module.deprecate('The module is using the PyOpenSSL backend. This backend has been deprecated',
2706                                  version='2.13', collection_name='ansible.builtin')
2707                 if provider == 'selfsigned':
2708                     certificate = SelfSignedCertificate(module)
2709                 elif provider == 'acme':
2710                     certificate = AcmeCertificate(module, 'pyopenssl')
2711                 elif provider == 'ownca':
2712                     certificate = OwnCACertificate(module)
2713                 elif provider == 'entrust':
2714                     certificate = EntrustCertificate(module, 'pyopenssl')
2715                 else:
2716                     certificate = AssertOnlyCertificate(module)
2717             elif backend == 'cryptography':
2718                 if not CRYPTOGRAPHY_FOUND:
2719                     module.fail_json(msg=missing_required_lib('cryptography >= {0}'.format(MINIMAL_CRYPTOGRAPHY_VERSION)),
2720                                      exception=CRYPTOGRAPHY_IMP_ERR)
2721                 if module.params['selfsigned_version'] == 2 or module.params['ownca_version'] == 2:
2722                     module.fail_json(msg='The cryptography backend does not support v2 certificates, '
2723                                          'use select_crypto_backend=pyopenssl for v2 certificates')
2724                 if provider == 'selfsigned':
2725                     certificate = SelfSignedCertificateCryptography(module)
2726                 elif provider == 'acme':
2727                     certificate = AcmeCertificate(module, 'cryptography')
2728                 elif provider == 'ownca':
2729                     certificate = OwnCACertificateCryptography(module)
2730                 elif provider == 'entrust':
2731                     certificate = EntrustCertificate(module, 'cryptography')
2732                 else:
2733                     certificate = AssertOnlyCertificateCryptography(module)
2734 
2735         if module.params['state'] == 'present':
2736             if module.check_mode:
2737                 result = certificate.dump(check_mode=True)
2738                 result['changed'] = module.params['force'] or not certificate.check(module)
2739                 module.exit_json(**result)
2740 
2741             certificate.generate(module)
2742         else:
2743             if module.check_mode:
2744                 result = certificate.dump(check_mode=True)
2745                 result['changed'] = os.path.exists(module.params['path'])
2746                 module.exit_json(**result)
2747 
2748             certificate.remove(module)
2749 
2750         result = certificate.dump()
2751         module.exit_json(**result)
2752     except crypto_utils.OpenSSLObjectError as exc:
2753         module.fail_json(msg=to_native(exc))
